Package: heuristr
Title: To make easier quantitative analysis from Heurist databases
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Aliette", "Roux", email = "aliette.roux@univ-nantes.fr",role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: So far, this package contains only one function : hr_import(). This function reads XML files exported from Heurist (https://heuristnetwork.org/) to build as many dataframes as 'record types' are used in the Heurist database. Each Heurist 'record type' matches a dataframe ; each Heurist 'record' matches a row in a dataframe. Furthermore, this function builds two other dataframes describing fields (type, help text, requirement, repeatability...) and vocabularies.
